{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 15:10:30.049441", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nExecutive summary\\n- The Clos fabric’s control plane (EBGP) and inter-router forwarding appear healthy.\\n- The endpoint pc_0_0 is down/unreachable at L2/L3. This is the only observed failure and explains failed host-to-host connectivity to 10.0.0.2.\\n- Impact is isolated to reachability of pc_0_0; other components (pc_0_1 and all routers) are operating normally.\\n\\nExpected behavior\\n- Each leaf advertises its directly connected /24 via EBGP.\\n- Spines peer with super-spine and leaves; super-spine peers with all spines.\\n- Hosts should be able to reach each other across the fabric (e.g., pc_0_1: 10.0.1.2 ↔ pc_0_0: 10.0.0.2).\\n\\nTests performed and key observations\\n1) Control-plane/BGP health\\n- BGP summaries on all routers are up with expected peers:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): 4 neighbors up; receiving 7 prefixes from each.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): 4 neighbors up; receiving 7 prefixes from each.\\n  - spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100): 6 neighbors up; receiving prefixes from leaves and super-spine.\\n  - spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101): 6 neighbors up; receiving prefixes from leaves and super-spine.\\n  - super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): 8 neighbors up; receiving prefixes as expected.\\n- RIB samples:\\n  - spine_router_0_0 has BGP routes to 10.0.0.0/24 via leaf_router_0_0 and 10.0.1.0/24 via leaf_router_0_1. Multiple other /24s are present as well, indicating proper distribution.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 learns 10.0.0.0/24 via a spine and has 10.0.1.0/24 as directly connected.\\n\\n2) Data-plane checks\\n- pc_0_1 host config:\\n  - IP 10.0.1.2/24, default via 10.0.1.1 (leaf_router_0_1). It successfully pings its gateway (10.0.1.1), indicating a healthy local L2 and L3 path.\\n- pc_0_1 to leaf_router_0_0 SVI:\\n  - pc_0_1 can ping 10.0.0.1 (leaf_router_0_0 SVI) successfully, proving the fabric data plane between pods/leaves is working.\\n- pc_0_1 to pc_0_0:\\n  - pc_0_1 cannot ping 10.0.0.2 (pc_0_0). 100% loss observed.\\n- leaf_router_0_0 toward pc_0_0:\\n  - Interface eth4 (10.0.0.1/24) is UP/LOWER_UP.\\n  - ARP for 10.0.0.2 fails (ip neigh shows FAILED; arping returns 100% unanswered).\\n- Tool errors when querying pc_0_0:\\n  - Direct operations against pc_0_0 (get_host_net_config, ping_pair with pc_0_0) fail with “container is not running,” indicating the host VM/container is down.\\n\\nAnomalies detected\\n- pc_0_0 is not operational:\\n  - Container not running errors during tool invocation.\\n  - ARP resolution to 10.0.0.2 fails on leaf_router_0_0.\\n  - End-to-end ping to 10.0.0.2 fails from pc_0_1, while ping to 10.0.0.1 succeeds.\\n\\nScope and localization\\n- Fault localized to the end-host pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2) or its immediate L2 adjacency.\\n- The fabric (leafs, spines, super-spine) shows:\\n  - All BGP sessions up.\\n  - Correct routes in RIBs.\\n  - Successful inter-leaf connectivity as evidenced by pc_0_1 reaching 10.0.0.1.\\n\\nProbable root cause\\n- pc_0_0 is powered off/not running, resulting in no ARP response on 10.0.0.0/24 and complete loss of reachability to 10.0.0.2. The fabric control and data planes are healthy otherwise.\\n\\nImpact assessment\\n- Loss of connectivity to pc_0_0 only.\\n- No observed impact on routing stability or reachability to other subnets/hosts (pc_0_1 is unaffected)., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='3b8e4656-f0c7-46ef-87c1-77245e304217'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
